  "texts": [
    "NotationThe following notation will be used throughout.Notation 1.4 (Posets and Relations).",
    "For a poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩ and x, y ∈ S:1.",
    "↓x = {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ x};2. x ≬ y iff ∃z ∈ S: z ⊑ x and z ⊑ y (\"x and y are compatible\"); 3. x ⊥ y iff not x ≬ y (\"x and y are incompatible\").For a binary relation R on S, X ⊆ S, and x ∈ S: 4.",
    "R[X] is the image of X under R, i.e., R[X] = {y ∈ S | ∃x ∈ X: xRy};5.",
    "R -1 [X] is the preimage of X under R, i.e., R -1 [X] = {y ∈ S | ∃x ∈ X: yRx};6."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}